Yes, there is an answer. We plan to write an article about it in future.

I'll include a mini-spoiler, since you asked:

+Spoiler

-text


Somewhere else, an individual found three  a mystery for now, unless you really want to know). They had been passed down from generation to generation (he is related to SCP-3574-C).

When he found them, he unintentionally activated their anomalous property. All three will foretell a terrible future, then each will state methods to prevent it, but only one method is correct. Performing the other two methods (or not doing anything) will result in the tragedy happening.

The Foundation contained these three . Furthermore, they state that something terrible will happen, unless the fourth one is found and contained.

While the first three  simply foretell tragedies, and ways to prevent them, the fourth is malevolent, and causes these tragedies, to feed off misfortune.

Neither the individual, nor the group related to SCP-3574 knew about the existence of each other's . They were created by their ancestor, to save them from persecution, or some other reason, which we haven't decided.

The nature of the  is hinted in the pictures of the decapitated goat heads, that accompany the riddle.








